                        <summary/>
                        <msItem xml:id="ms_i1">
                            <locus from="1r" to="27r"/>
                            <title type="complete" ref="LIT1285Dersan" xml:lang="gez">ድርሳን፡ ዘደረሰ፡
                                ቅዱስ፡ <persName ref="PRS10382Yohanne">ዮሐንስ፡</persName> ኤጲስ፡ ቆጶስ፡
                                በእንተ፡ ዕበዩ፡ ወክብሩ፡ ለቅዱስ፡ <persName ref="PRS4523Garima"
                                >ይስሐቅ</persName>።</title>
                            <explicit xml:lang="gez"><locus from="26vb" to="27ra"/> ወዘንተ፡ ብሂሎ፡ ተሰወረ፡
                                እምኔሆሙ፡ ወኢርእይዎ፡ ደግመ። ወፈጸመ፡ ገድሎ፡ አመ፡ ፲ወ፯፡ ለወርኃ፡ ሰኔ። ጸሎቱ፡ ወበረከቱ፡ ትዕቀበነ፡
                                ለዓለመ፡ ዓለም፡ አሜን። ለይኩን። ለይኩን። </explicit>
                            <note>The homily edited in <bibl>
                                    <ptr target="bm:ContiRossini1898Garima"
                                        /><citedRange>171-178</citedRange>
                                </bibl> continues for about one more page, with the last lines of
                                the present manuscript corresponding to line 637 of the edition.
                                Cataloguing this manuscript, <persName ref="PRS3182ContiRo"/> noted
                                about himself that <cit>
                                    <quote>text not used by Conti Rossini</quote>
                                </cit>(<cit>
                                    <quote xml:lang="fr">texte non untilisé par Conti
                                        Rossini.</quote>
                                </cit>) The scholar adds the following comment: <cit>
                                    <quote>It contains the story of the serpent king of the land of
                                        Agʿāzi <foreign xml:lang="gez">ብሔረ፡ አግዓዚ፡</foreign>, but the
                                        records of land grants seem to be missing. The final account
                                        of the misfortunes that were to strike the <placeName
                                            ref="LOC2254DabraD">monastery of Dāmmo</placeName> is
                                        also absent; it is evident that this is a later addition,
                                        most likely referring to the devastation caused by the
                                        Catholics at <placeName ref="LOC2866EndaAb">Endā abbā
                                            Garimā</placeName> (see, for example, <bibl><ptr
                                                target="bm:Vitelleschi1628Lettere"/><citedRange
                                                unit="part">first letter</citedRange></bibl>.
                                        Obviously, the <ref type="mss"
                                            corresp="PetermannIINachtrag28">ms. Peterm. II Nachtr.
                                            28</ref> in Berlin, which contains this account, cannot
                                        be from the 16th century, as <persName ref="PRS3562Dillmann"
                                            >Aug. Dillmann</persName> believed. However, it already
                                        includes the curse: "May your offering be like the offering
                                        of Rome" (see <bibl>
                                            <ptr target="bm:ContiRossini1898Garima"/>
                                            <citedRange unit="line">524-525</citedRange>
                                        </bibl>). It should be noted that the <foreign
                                            xml:lang="gez">gadl</foreign> in our manuscript begins
                                        with the well-known formula from the time of King <persName
                                            ref="PRS10626ZaraY">Zarʾa Yāʿqob</persName>: <foreign
                                            xml:lang="gez">በስመ፡ አብ፡, etc. በቅድስት፡ ሥላሴ፡ እንዘ፡ እት<gap
                                                reason="illegible"/>፡ ወእትመኀፀን፡ እክሕደከ፡ ሰይጣን፡ በቅድመ፡
                                            ይእቲ፡ እምየ፡</foreign> which would confirm the age of this
                                        work.</quote>
                                </cit>(<cit>
                                    <quote xml:lang="fr">On y trouve le récit du serpent roi de la
                                        terre d'Agʿāzi, <foreign xml:lang="gez">ብሔረ፡
                                        አግዓዚ፡</foreign>, mais les concessions des fiefs semblent
                                        manquer. Le récit final sur les malheurs qui devront frapper
                                            <placeName ref="LOC2254DabraD">le couvent de
                                            Dāmo</placeName> manque aussi; on voit qu'il s'agit
                                        d'une addition plus récent, qui vise sans doute les ravages
                                        des catholiques à <placeName ref="LOC2866EndaAb">Endā abbā
                                            Garimā </placeName> (voir p.ex. <title>Lettre annue di
                                            Ethiopia del 1624, 1625 e 1626, Rome, 1628, première
                                            lettre</title>). Évidemment, le <ref type="mss"
                                            corresp="PetermannIINachtrag28">ms. Peterm. II Nachtr.
                                            28</ref> de Berlin, qui contient ce récit, ne peut pas
                                        être du XVI siècle, comme le croyait <persName
                                            ref="PRS3562Dillmann">Aug. Dillmann</persName>. Mais on
                                        y trouve déjà la malédiction "que votre offrande soit comme
                                        l'offrande de Rome"; voir <bibl>
                                            <ptr target="bm:ContiRossini1898Garima"/><citedRange
                                                unit="line"> 524-525.</citedRange></bibl> Noter que
                                        le <foreign xml:lang="gez">gadl</foreign>, dans notre
                                        manuscrit, commence avec la formule bien connu du temps du
                                        roi <persName ref="PRS10626ZaraY">Zarʾa Yāʿqob:</persName>
                                        <foreign xml:lang="gez">በስመ፡ አብ፡, etc. በቅድስት፡ ሥላሴ፡ እንዘ፡
                                            እት///፡ ወእትመኀፀን፡ እክሕደከ፡ ሰይጣን፡ በቅድመ፡ ይእቲ፡ እምየ፡ </foreign>,
                                        ce qui confirmerait l'âge de cet ouvrage.</quote>
                                </cit>)</note>
                            <explicit xml:lang="gez" type="subscriptio">ዛቲ፡ መጽሐፍ፡ መጽሐፈ፡ ገድሉ፡ ለአባ፡
                                ገሪማ። ዘአጽሐፈ፡ አቡነ፡ ሃብተ፡ ገብርኤል፡ ከመ፡ ይኩኖ፡ መድኀኒተ፡ ነፍሱ፡ ለአቤት፡ ዘወሀበ፡ ለደሴተ፡
                                ጸጋ፡ ለእስጢፋኖስ፡ ለዘ፡ ጸሐፎ፡ ወለዘ፡ አጽሐፎ፡ ለዘ፡ አንበቦ፡ ወተርጎሞ፡ ወለዘ፡ ሰምዓ፡ ቃላቲሁ፡
                                ሕቡረ፡ ይምሕረነ፡ ለዓለመ፡ ዓለም፡ አሜን። ወአሜን። ለይኩን። <foreign xml:lang="fr"
                                    resp="PRS3182ContiRo">Ce livre est le livre des <title>Actes
                                        d'abbā Garimā</title>, qu'a fait écrire l'abuna <persName
                                        ref="PRS14709HabtaG">Habta Gabrʾēl</persName>, afin qu'il
                                    serve au salut de l'âme d'Abēt (?) qui l'a donné à <placeName
                                        ref="LOC2422DagaEs">l'île de Dāgā, à Estèves</placeName>;
                                    pour l'a écrit, etc.</foreign>
                                <foreign xml:lang="en">This book is the <title>Book of the Acts of
                                        Abbā Garimā</title>, commissioned by Abuna <persName
                                        ref="PRS14709HabtaG">Habta Gabrʾēl</persName> so that it may
                                    serve for the salvation of the soul of Abēt (?), who donated it
                                    to the <placeName ref="LOC2422DagaEs">island of Dāgā, to
                                        Estèves</placeName>; for the one who copied it etc.
                                </foreign>
                            </explicit>

                            <note>While cataloguing this manuscript, <persName ref="PRS3182ContiRo"
                                /> interpreted this note as an explicit. However, since it varies
                                from manuscript to manuscript and does not seem belonging to the
                                main text, it should rather be understood as a subscription.</note>
